

1. sudo bang bang (!!) Command
The bang bang (!!) command is a shortcut to repeat the previous command you entered in your terminal. This command is very useful when you forget that you need admin rights to make a certain action, and lets you repeat it with super-user rights just by typing

$ apt install git
E: Could not open lock file /var/lib/dpkg/lock - open (13: Permission denied)
E: Unable to lock the administration directory (/var/lib/dpkg/), are you root?

$ sudo !!
sudo apt install git

2. Killing and yanking text

Command is:
$find /var/log -type f -mtime +1 | xargs ls -lah | awk '{print $9}'

Use (ctrl+k) : Clear all AFTER cursor
$find /var/log -type f -mtime +1 


Back to previous (ctrl+y) : Paste (if you used a previous command to delete)
$find /var/log -type f -mtime +1 | xargs ls -lah | awk '{print $9}'

Use (ctrl+u) : Clear all BEFORE cursor
| xargs ls -lah | awk '{print $9}'

Shortcuts:

ctrl+w : Delete the word BEFORE the cursor
ctrl+a : Goto BEGINNING of command line
ctrl+e : Goto END of command line
ctrl+b : move back one character
ctrl+f : move forward one character
alt+f  : move cursor FORWARD one word
alt+b  : move cursor BACK one word
ctrl+l : Clear the screen (same as clear command)

